I really love the crepes here and at their nostrand location. I always get the salmon and cream cheese and I really think they do a good job with their iced latte. The sweet crepes are good too. I like this location a little more since it's less known than the other one, there are fewer people and they have outdoor seating! They made it into a cute garden looking spot and they have a cafe cat who comes around to say hi but is by no means aggressive. Prices are the same as the other location. I definitely recommend, especially in the summer if you want to sit outdoors.

Pretty much everything is really good! Not a huge fan of the smoothies though. If you add protein expect like 5g which is basically nothing. Every time I get them, they are aren't really smoothie consistency. Also, I wanted to replace peanut butter with oats in one of their choices and I got charged extra for it without being told so that's annoying. I feel like I'm getting a deli/corner store made smoothie with protein but paying $8.

This is the best place in Brooklyn for a coffee, crepe, croissant, juice, savory foods and more, in addition to and excellent service from a really cool and very friendly team, who really make my day every time I see them! I’ve been coming here for over a year 4-5 times a week and it’s literally the best cafe I’ve ever been to. I’m a bit of a cafe junkie, and the moment I started coming here it became my cafe home. I feel comfortable, I get a lot of work done,  my daughter gets her homework done, the customer service is OUTSTANDING & the food and smoothies are delicious. Free WiFi, plenty of seating even if they get busy and they keep it clean. I love this spot, it’s  jewel.

I love this place! There are at least three different branches in Brooklyn and I've visited each of them. The crepes are to die for! The people are also very welcoming.

This lovely little cafe/ crepe shop is truly a neighborhood gem! Inside it's cozy and inviting, with little tables and seating areas for patrons to work or dine. It has a slight coffee shop vibe :) . Their menu offers everything from specialty crepes, baked goods, salads and sandwiches as well as coffees, teas and smoothies. I'm a big fan of their crepes and also their savory croissants. I've noticed there's normally a pretty steady stream of regulars who come in and they even have a sister shop akin to this one just down the block on Nostrand Avenue. If you're in the area it's definitely worth checking out - the menu is broad and there's a little something for everyone.

This place is my favorite spot in Bed Stuy to read, work, or grab an on-the-go pastry. The staff is sweet, they bump an awesome assortment of African pop tunes, recent and more vintage, and all of that is not too talk of the *delicious* crepes, health juices (hangover tested - A grade), and other food and drink offerings. If remote work is your cup of tea, this is where you'll want to get your cup of coffee.  I highly recommend a pastry, juice, or smoothie if you're on the go - their crepes are a little large for a walking snack. The Pain Au Chocolate is a personal favorite. As Crepes go, the salmon options are ah-mazing, as is the classic ham and cheese!

Needs improvement 1. Needs free WiFi 2. I ordered an iced coffee and pointed to it on the menu but got hot coffee instead. When I reminded her, she gave me hot coffe with a few ice cubes..  So my iced  coffee was lukewarm. I returned the drink again asking for more ice & they gave me back an overflowing beverage... the iced coffe is decent.  Good coffee potency, but lacking in flavor.  This is supposed to be mocha iced coffee & she clearly forgot the mocha flavoring. Really deserves 2 stars for experience but they're Black-owned & clearly very new & inexperienced so in a few months i will come back & give them another chance.  Atmosphere is great though... place is clean & new & there's an outdoor patio which is great for summer.
